  "local_port": 47844,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How does one configure TCS mail on an iPhone?",
  "response": "To configure TCS Mail on your iPhone, follow these steps:\n\n### Step 1: Open Settings\n1. Unlock your iPhone and navigate to the **Settings** app.\n\n### Step 2: Add Account\n2. Scroll down and tap on **Mail**.\n3. Tap on **Accounts**.\n4. Tap on **Add Account**.\n\n### Step 3: Choose Exchange\n5. Select **Exchange** from the list of email providers.\n\n### Step 4: Enter Account Information\n6. Enter your TCS email address in the **Email** field.\n7. Enter your TCS password in the **Password** field.\n8. Tap **Next** in the top right corner.\n\n### Step 5: Configure Exchange Settings\n9. If prompted, enter a description for the account (e.g., \"TCS Mail\").\n10. In the **Server** field, enter `outlook.office365.com`.\n11. In the **Domain** field, leave it blank.\n12. In the **Username** field, enter your full TCS email address again.\n13. Ensure the **Password** field is filled with your TCS password.\n14. Tap **Next** in the top right corner.\n\n### Step 6: Enable Services\n15. Choose the services you want to sync with your iPhone (Mail, Contacts, Calendars, Reminders, and Notes). It's recommended to enable at least **Mail**.\n16. Tap **Save** in the top right corner.\n\n### Step 7: Verify Configuration\n17. Go back to the home screen and open the **Mail** app.\n18. Check if your TCS Mail account is listed and if you can send and receive emails.\n\nIf you encounter any issues during the setup, ensure that your internet connection is stable and that your TCS credentials are correct. If problems persist, you may need to contact TCS IT support for further assistance.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to successfully configure TCS Mail on your iPhone.",
